content.description: Look for the obvious right leaning arch and find the left facing dihedral to the right of the arch.  The climb heads up the slab just right of this dihedral into a left leaning hand crack.  The first pro is here and the crux is moving over a slight bulge into the crack.  Trend up and left to a small ledge.  Head up the slab trending left of a small roof.  A 5.easy crack heads to a large belay ledge with a good crack for gear to the climbers right.
